<TITLE> Tarique release 'reflects rule of law': Speaker </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 3 (bdnews24.com)  Speaker Jamiruddin Sircar said Wednesday the release of BNP senior joint secretary general Tarique Rahman "reflected the rule of law". "Tarique secured bail in all cases against him. The government released him in line with the court orders. It reflects the rule of law," Sircar told bdnews24.com after visiting Tarique at Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University hospital hours after the release. The speaker, accompanied by deputy speaker Akter Hamid Siddiqui, went to the hospital around 9pm, staying there for 25 minutes. Sircar said visiting Tarique was a courtesy call. He said there was no politics during the visit. Speaking of Tarique's mother, the still detained ex-prime minister Khaleda Zia, Sircar told bdnews24.com: "I hope the government will release her too." bdnews24.
